('62f9cd53f3a3f', 'Teacherbot Model based-on Automatic Question Generation for Cyber Education', 'teacherbot-model-based-on-automatic-question-generation-for-cyber-education', 'This study is focused on addressing the tasks of developing learning objects and media delivery using digital education technology.   The proliferated digital transformation in education domain has caused some disrupted changes in higher education system. This study is focused on addressing the tasks of developing learning objects and media delivery using digital education technology. The purposes of this research are two folds. First, developing a question generation-based TeacherBot for constructing questions that require in-depth answers to leverage teacher and student engagement productivity in a pedagogical context when they seek to explore broader and deeper knowledge.', '<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>This study is focused on addressing the tasks of developing learning objects and media delivery using digital education technology.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>The proliferated digital transformation in education domain has caused some disrupted changes in higher education system. This study is focused on addressing the tasks of developing learning objects and media delivery using digital education technology. The purposes of this research are two folds. First, developing a question generation-based TeacherBot for constructing questions that require in-depth answers to leverage teacher and student engagement productivity in a pedagogical context when they seek to explore broader and deeper knowledge. Second, evaluating acceptance of the generated questions produced by the Teacherbot moodel using BLEU and Cohen&rsquo;s Kappa score measurements. In addition, measuring the impact of the generated questions adption on learning using the Kirkpatrick evaluatin framework which includes: Student Reaction Evaluation, Learning Transfer Evaluation, Student Behavior Change, Performance Impact Evaluation. Some experimentation results showed some evidences that the question generation-based TeacherBot which was implemented using Text-to-Text Transfer Transformer (T5) approach achieved good results. Using 100 questions as samples, the measurement results achieved BLEU score = 0.92 and a Cohen&rsquo;s Kappa coefficient = 0.60 which means that the questions generated by Question Generation can be understood by readers or users. Meanwhile, the results of the evaluation using the Kirkpatrick framework showed a score of 4.111, which means that Teacherbot built based on the</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>Question Generation model can be recommended for learning in various fields of science and knowledge.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>Keywords&mdash;Artificial Intelligence; Question Generator; Teacherbot; Transformer; T5.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nHalo teman ICE Institute!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ICE Institute telah melakukan penelitian kolaborasi dengan Universitas Terbuka (UT) dan Binus University&nbsp;dengan judul:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"background-color:#e74c3c\">Teacherbot Model based-on Automatic Question Generation for Cyber Education</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Penelitian secara menyeluruh dapat diakses dengan<span style=\"color:#3498db\"> </span><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1a5IQhtnMteeMw-uk14fZl_FH358I2vt-/view?usp=sharing\"><span style=\"color:#3498db\">klik tulisan ini ya!</span></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Penelitian juga dapat dilihat dengan mengunjungi Pameran Hakteknas yang bisa diakses lewat <a href=\"http://expo.icei.ac.id\"><span style=\"color:#3498db\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\">expo.icei.ac.id</span></span></a>&nbsp;sampai dengan 31 Agustus!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Selamat membaca!</p>\r\n', 'teacherbot,research,PenelitianKolaborasi,ICEInstitute,ArtificialIntelligence', 7, 27, 2, 'post', '62f9cd53f3a3f.png', '2022-08-15 12:36:36', '2022-08-15 05:03:37', 188),
('62f9dd562d9da', 'Learners’ Online Self-Regulated Learning Skills in Indonesia Open University: Implications for Policies and Practice', 'learners-online-self-regulated-learning-skills-in-indonesia-open-university-implications-for-policies-and-practice', 'Research Topics at ICE Institute', '<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>This study examined how students with different demographic backgrounds adopt or fail to adopt self-regulated learning to engage in online distance learning. Survey data were collected from 295 students at Indonesia Open University.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>To succeed in online distance learning where students are physically separated from teachers and peers, students must develop self-regulated learning skills to effectively manage their learning process. This study examined how students with different demographic backgrounds adopt or fail to adopt self-regulated learning to engage in online distance learning. Survey data were collected from 295 students at Indonesia Open University. Although students&rsquo; online learning self-efficacy and online self-regulated learning were above average, they reported low levels of confidence and abilities to seek help, develop task strategies, and allocate time for online learning. Their online self-regulated learning and online learning self-efficacy were significantly correlated. However, there were no significant relationships between online self-regulated learning and learning performance, and between online learning self-efficacy and learning performance. Furthermore, female and/or older students reported lower learning performance than male and younger students. Qualitative data from open-ended questions were analyzed to interpret the quantitative results. Recommendations for stakeholders of open universities were made to assist in students&rsquo; improvement of self-regulated learning skills and to address equity issues in Indonesian online distance learning and similar contexts.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Keywords: open university; online distance learning; online self-regulated learning; online learning self-efficacy</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Halo teman ICE Institute!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ICE Institute telah melakukan penelitian kolaborasi dengan Universitas Terbuka (UT), Seamolec, Universitas Indonesia (UI) dan The Education University of Hong Kong&nbsp;dengan judul:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"background-color:#e74c3c\">Learners&rsquo; Online Self-Regulated Learning Skills in Indonesia Open University: Implications for Policies and Practice</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Penelitian secara menyeluruh dapat diakses dengan <a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1v8LEzhIRP4Gzel_QSK7S8d2MgaubvB_t/view?usp=sharing\">klik tulisan ini ya!</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Penelitian juga dapat dilihat dengan mengunjungi Pameran Hakteknas yang bisa diakses lewat <a href=\"http://www.expo.icei.ac.id\">www.expo.icei.ac.id</a>&nbsp;sampai dengan 31 Agustus!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Selamat membaca!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'penelitian kolaborasi,ice institute,self-regulated learning,universitas terbuka,universitas indonesia,seamolec,the education university of hong kong', 7, 27, 2, 'delete', '62f9dd562d9da.png', '2022-08-15 01:44:54', '2022-08-15 05:44:54', 0),
('62f9e0212d2c0', 'Pengalaman Sosioemosional Mahasiswa dalam Pembelajaran Daring', 'pengalaman-sosioemosional-mahasiswa-dalam-pembelajaran-daring', 'This study provided empirical information on how ICE Institute as a digital marketplace system and its online courses collections can redesign itself to provide students with a positive and meaningful experience. Indonesia Cyber Education Institute is a newly launched digital marketplace for online courses in Indonesia. It carries the functions of curating, verifying, and registering online courses, managing the gallery, researching, and innovating online learning, partnership, and credentials, and linking to the job market. At present, it has a network of 13 higher education institutions, one professional association, and EdX Consortium to collect 1546 online courses serving 3319 students. ', '<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>This study provided empirical information on how ICE Institute as a digital marketplace system and its online courses collections can redesign itself to provide students with a positive and meaningful experience.&nbsp;Indonesia Cyber Education Institute is a newly launched digital marketplace for online courses in Indonesia. It carries the functions of curating, verifying, and registering online courses, managing the gallery, researching, and innovating online learning, partnership, and credentials, and linking to the job market. At present, it has a network of 13 higher education institutions, one professional association, and EdX Consortium to collect 1546 online courses serving 3319 students.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>As a new system, ICE Institute needs to document its users&#39; experience as they interact with its system and its online courses collections. Users are to come to the ICE Institute system to take online courses with full expectations for positive experiences. As such, it is necessary for ICE Institute to provide a baseline of good experience as a differentiator and as the expected minimum quality of the ICE Institute system. Various studies show that users are likely to leave the digital system/products if they find difficulties or troubles or run into a usability problem.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>User experience, according to Feng &amp; Wei (2019) is a concept that includes all aspects of how individuals interact with a digital product, and it is highly context-dependent and dynamic. Roto, et al. (2011)2 asserts that User Experience (UX) research focusing on the emotional and experiential aspects of system usage is highly recognized relevance for evaluating the user&#39;s experience. UX research explores the relationships between usability, symbolic, and aesthetic value for user experience with products (Feng &amp; Wei, 2019).</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>This study evaluates the experience of higher education students in Indonesia as users of the ICE</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>Institute system and its online courses collections. Specifically, it will look at how students value their emotional and experiential aspects of their online experience. Data for this study is collected using AttrakDiff questionnaire that has been translated into Bahasa Indonesia. The AttrakDiff is a method developed by Hassenzahl et al to assess the perceived pragmatic quality, the hedonic quality, and the attractiveness of the interactive digital product. Feng and Wei (2019) state that the AttrakDiff questionnaire is a well-established UX evaluation method and can be applied to a wide range of digital products; and also, in the context of users&rsquo; initial encounters with the digital product, as well as to evaluate the users&rsquo; interaction with the digital product.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>The AttrakDiff questionnaire consists of four parts to tap the attractiveness, hedonic quality-identification, hedonic quality-stimulation, dan pragmatic quality of the student&#39;s experience. Each part measures the attributes utilizing the bipolar semantic differential 7-scale method that represent opposites (bad-good). The AttrakDiff questionnaire is distributed for a one-shot survey to 30% of ICE Institute&#39;s users and 30% of SPADA Indonesia users participating in this study. Users of SPADA Indonesia &ndash; another online courses aggregator that was established in 2014 for the purpose of provision of online resources to implement blended learning in Indonesia &ndash; are also surveyed to provide a comparative perspective. Quantitative analysis is employed to analyze data collected in this study, especially to identify differences in emotional and experiential aspects of students&#39; experience, both the ICE Institute students and the SPADA Indonesia students. Further analysis will be employed to identify the most influential factor in students&#39; online courses experience. The results of this study provide empirical information on how ICE Institute as a digital marketplace system and its online courses collections can redesign itself to provide students with a positive and meaningful experience.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Halo teman ICE Institute!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ICE Institute telah melakukan penelitian kolaborasi dengan Universitas Terbuka (UT) dan Kementrian Pendidikan dan Budaya (Kemendikbud) dengan judul:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"background-color:#e74c3c\">Pengalaman Sosioemosional Mahasiswa dalam Pembelajaran Daring</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Penelitian secara menyeluruh dapat diakses dengan <a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1QQKG8ol2MpzaIYsG8gc8TUib3KJB7nac/view?usp=sharing\"><span style=\"color:#3498db\">klik tulisan ini ya!</span></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Penelitian juga dapat dilihat dengan mengunjungi Pameran Hakteknas yang bisa diakses lewat <a href=\"http://www.expo.icei.ac.id\"><span style=\"color:#3498db\">www.expo.icei.ac.id</span></a>&nbsp;sampai dengan 31 Agustus!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Selamat membaca!</p>\r\n', 'research,SelfRegulatedLearning,Sosioemosional,PenelitianKolaborasi,ICEInstitute', 7, 27, 2, 'post', '62f9e0212d2c0.png', '2022-08-15 01:56:49', '2022-08-15 05:05:16', 254),
('62f9e1e1979ac', 'Design of Student Character Development Model Based on the Habituation Method on a Mobile Device Platform', 'design-of-student-character-development-model-based-on-the-habituation-method-on-a-mobile-device-platform', 'The development of learning technology cannot be separated from breakthroughs made by experts in technology and education. This paper discusses the design of student character development models through students\' daily activities at home and outside school. ', '<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>The development of learning technology cannot be separated from breakthroughs made by experts in technology and education. This paper discusses the design of student character development models through students&#39;&nbsp;daily activities at home and outside school. The model is implemented into a server-connected mobile application. The system performs automatic evaluations regularly according to the given settings. The system also allows teachers to monitor student progress and provide feedback to students and parents. The character development method used in the model is habituation. The habituation process is shown by doing activities regularly and repeatedly. The application was currently being tested as a pilot project in one of the Islamic Elementary Schools in Bandung, West Java, Indonesia. The method used to prove the effectiveness and efficiency of the application is the mixed method. Questionnaires were given to parents and teachers. Interviews were conducted with teachers. The result showed that implementing a character development model based on the habituation method on a mobile device platform proved to be more effective and efficient for helping teachers monitor and evaluate the development of student attitudes or character development. It^s easier for parents and students to document the activities routinely and repetitively. The evaluation results showed that 89% of students regularly carried out and reported activities using the application. It showed that 89% of students had achieved the responding level based on bloom^s taxonomy of affective aspects.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>Keywords: character development- habituation- affective- role model- education technology</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>Topic: Character Building</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Halo teman ICE Institute!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ICE Institute telah melakukan penelitian kolaborasi dengan Universitas Terbuka (UT), Universitas Muhammadiyah, Institut Teknologi Garut, dan Institut Teknologi Bandung&nbsp;dengan judul:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Design of Student Character Development Model Based on the Habituation Method on a Mobile Device Platform</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Penelitian secara menyeluruh dapat diakses dengan <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1BX8mDFbrn4Wb7t9U-qH1uK9u4oeWm9il/edit?usp=sharing&amp;ouid=108116126261950449175&amp;rtpof=true&amp;sd=true\"><span style=\"color:#3498db\">klik tulisan ini ya!</span></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Penelitian juga dapat dilihat dengan mengunjungi Pameran Hakteknas yang bisa diakses lewat <a href=\"http://expo.icei.ac.id\"><span style=\"color:#3498db\">expo.icei.ac.id</span></a><span style=\"color:#3498db\">&nbsp;</span>sampai dengan 31 Agustus!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Selamat membaca!</p>\r\n', 'CharacterDevelopmentModel,PenelitianKolaborasi,research,ICEInstitute,EducationTechnology', 7, 27, 2, 'post', '62f9e1e1979ac.png', '2022-08-15 02:04:17', '2022-08-15 05:05:50', 264),
('62f9e2f228e37', 'Learners’ Online Self-Regulated Learning Skills in Indonesia Open University', 'learners-online-self-regulated-learning-skills-in-indonesia-open-university', 'This study examined how students with different demographic backgrounds adopt or fail to adopt self-regulated learning to engage in online distance learning. Survey data were collected from 295 students at Indonesia Open University.', '<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>This study examined how students with different demographic backgrounds adopt or fail to adopt self-regulated learning to engage in online distance learning. Survey data were collected from 295 students at Indonesia Open University.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>To succeed in online distance learning where students are physically separated from teachers and peers, students must develop self-regulated learning skills to effectively manage their learning process. This study examined how students with different demographic backgrounds adopt or fail to adopt self-regulated learning to engage in online distance learning. Survey data were collected from 295 students at Indonesia Open University. Although students&rsquo; online learning self-efficacy and online self-regulated learning were above average, they reported low levels of confidence and abilities to seek help, develop task strategies, and allocate time for online learning. Their online self-regulated learning and online learning self-efficacy were significantly correlated. However, there were no significant relationships between online self-regulated learning and learning performance, and between online learning self-efficacy and learning performance. Furthermore, female and/or older students reported lower learning performance than male and younger students. Qualitative data from open-ended questions were analyzed to interpret the quantitative results. Recommendations for stakeholders of open universities were made to assist in students&rsquo; improvement of self-regulated learning skills and to address equity issues in Indonesian online distance learning and similar contexts.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>Keywords: open university; online distance learning; online self-regulated learning; online learning self-efficacy</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Halo teman ICE Institute!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ICE Institute telah melakukan penelitian kolaborasi dengan Universitas Terbuka (UT), Universitas Indonesia, Seamolec, dan Education University of Hong Kong&nbsp;dengan judul:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"background-color:#e74c3c\">Learners&rsquo; Online Self-Regulated Learning Skills in Indonesia Open University: Implications for Policies and Practice</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Penelitian secara menyeluruh dapat diakses dengan <a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1v8LEzhIRP4Gzel_QSK7S8d2MgaubvB_t/view?usp=sharing\"><span style=\"color:#3498db\">klik tulisan ini ya!</span></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Penelitian juga dapat dilihat dengan mengunjungi Pameran Hakteknas yang bisa diakses lewat <a href=\"http://expo.icei.ac.id\"><span style=\"color:#3498db\">expo.icei.ac.id</span></a>&nbsp;sampai dengan 31 Agustus!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Selamat membaca!</p>\r\n', 'OnlineDistanceLearning,OnlineSelfRegulatedLearning,SelfEfficacy,PenelitianKolaborasi,research,ICEInstitute', 7, 27, 2, 'post', '62f9e2f228e37.png', '2022-08-15 02:08:50', '2022-08-15 04:33:40', 294),
('62f9eb8051d13', 'Evaluating Students\' Experience in Online Learning: The ICE Institute\'s Experience', 'evaluating-students-experience-in-online-learning-the-ice-institutes-experience', 'his study evaluates the experience of higher education students in Indonesia as users of the ICE Institute system and its online courses collections. ', '<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>Indonesia Cyber Education Institute is a newly launched digital marketplace for online courses in Indonesia. At present, it has a network of 13 higher education institutions, one professional association, and EdX Consortium to collect 1546 online courses serving 3319 students.This study evaluates the experience of higher education students in Indonesia as users of the ICE Institute system and its online courses collections. It looks at users&rsquo; emotional and experiential aspects of their online experience. Data is collected using translated AttrakDiff questionnaire to tap the attractiveness, hedonic quality-identification, hedonic quality-stimulation, and pragmatic quality of the student&#39;s experience. All attributes are measured using the bipolar semantic differential 7-scale to represent opposites (bad-good). The questionnaire is distributed for a one-shot survey to 30% of both ICE Institute and SPADA Indonesia users. Collected data is analyzed quantitatively to identify differences in emotional and experiential aspects, and to identify influential factors in students&#39; online experience. The results of this study will provide baseline information for ICE Institute redesign itself to provide students with a positive and meaningful experience.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>Keywords: ICE Institute; AttrakDiff; Online Learning, Indonesia&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Halo teman ICE Institute!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ICE Institute telah melakukan penelitian kolaborasi dengan Universitas Terbuka (UT) dan Kemenristekdikti dengan judul:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"background-color:#e74c3c\">Evaluating Students&#39; Experience in Online Learning: The ICE Institute&#39;s Experience</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Penelitian secara menyeluruh dapat diakses dengan <a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1fcJKm4-cMmU-CYlZtrBDJVNNo5E5DQOQ/view?usp=sharing\"><span style=\"color:#3498db\">klik tulisan ini ya!</span></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Penelitian juga dapat dilihat dengan mengunjungi Pameran Hakteknas yang bisa diakses lewat <a href=\"http://expo.icei.ac.id\"><span style=\"color:#3498db\">expo.icei.ac.id</span></a>&nbsp;sampai dengan 31 Agustus!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Selamat membaca!</p>\r\n', 'PenelitianKolaborasi,research,ICEInstitute,AttrakDiff,OnlineLearning,studentsExperience', 7, 27, 2, 'post', '62f9eb8051d13.png', '2022-08-15 02:45:20', '2022-08-15 05:11:00', 199),
('62f9f0ae25fd1', 'Model Machine Learning untuk Memprediksi Kesuksesan Mahasiswa dalam Pembelajaran Daring', 'model-machine-learning-untuk-memprediksi-kesuksesan-mahasiswa-dalam-pembelajaran-daring', 'The model is based on students\' activities data in learning management systems (LMS) i.e., the number of accessing materials, student participation in discussion forum, and assignment scores.', '<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>The model is based on students&#39; activities data in learning management systems (LMS) i.e., the number of accessing materials, student participation in discussion forum, and assignment scores. Data are collected from 129 Universitas Terbuka&#39;s students who attend a course.&nbsp;Recently, machine learning in Learning Analytics (LA) has been implemented to measure student success in a course, including in online learning. By using student activity data, machine learning can be used to help lecturers to predict and classify student success based on their performance during the learning process. The ability to predict student success is beneficial as early warning for lecturers as well as for the students. In this research, a machine learning model based on Fuzzy KNN method is used to predict student success. The development of the model is based on students&#39; activities data in learning management systems (LMS) i.e., the number of accessing materials, student participation in discussion forum, and assignment scores. Data are collected from 129 Universitas Terbuka&#39;s students who attend a course. Those data are used for data training and data testing to build the model. In order to improve the result and to overcome the imbalanced data, the SMOTE method is applied. The model performance is measured based on accuracy, recall, precision, and F1-score with various numbers of neighbors in Fuzzy KNN.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>Keywords: Learning Analytic, Machine Learning, Learning Management Systems, ICE Institute, Learning Analytic, Machine Learning, Fuzzy KNN, Student Success</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Halo teman ICE Institute!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ICE Institute telah melakukan penelitian kolaborasi dengan Universitas Terbuka (UT) dan Universitas Indonesia (UI) dengan judul:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"background-color:#e74c3c\">Model Machine Learning untuk Memprediksi Kesuksesan Mahasiswa dalam Pembelajaran Daring</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Penelitian secara menyeluruh dapat diakses dengan <a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/10g4yfPP6D6Pbo3QUivpSVd2fCe2LsHuI/view?usp=sharing\">klik tulisan ini ya!</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Penelitian juga dapat dilihat dengan mengunjungi Pameran Hakteknas yang bisa diakses lewat <a href=\"http://www.expo.icei.ac.id\">www.expo.icei.ac.id</a>&nbsp;sampai dengan 31 Agustus!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Selamat membaca!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'PenelitianKolaborasi,MachineLearning,ICEInstitute,LearningAnalytic,StudentSuccess', 7, 27, 2, 'post', '62f9f0ae25fd1.png', '2022-08-15 03:07:26', '2022-08-15 04:34:55', 131),
('62f9f509b548d', 'E-learning Engagement Framework: Defining the Gap Between Teachers Activities and Students Expectation', 'e-learning-engagement-framework-defining-the-gap-between-teachers-activities-and-students-expectation', 'One of the important issues in the online learning model is related to the issue of engagement. Many parties find it very difficult to build engagement between educators and students in the learning process.', '<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>One of the important issues in the online learning model is related to the issue of engagement. Many parties find it very difficult to build engagement between educators and students in the learning process. Nevertheless, quite a lot of efforts and initiatives have been developed by education practitioners in introducing various techniques to build engagement in online learning environments. This study attempts to offer a model for measuring whether the efforts of these educators are bearing fruit or not. The model built in this study uses a gap analysis technique, which is to compare the various efforts of educators in building engagement and the opinions of students who experience the learning process firsthand. Through a number of comparison metrics it can be concluded whether the efforts in question have paid off or not. It is hoped that this model can help various parties who want to measure the effectiveness of various learning approaches from the engagement aspect.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>Index Terms&mdash;engagement, e-learning, measurement, frame- work, gap</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Halo teman ICE Institute!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ICE Institute telah melakukan penelitian kolaborasi dengan Universitas Terbuka (UT) dengan judul:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"background-color:#e74c3c\">E-learning Engagement Framework: Defining the Gap Between Teachers Activities and Students Expectation</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Penelitian secara menyeluruh dapat diakses dengan <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1WDdBDD5kE2qvFbqBCJ4mlfspr9YMH3_A/edit?usp=sharing&amp;ouid=108116126261950449175&amp;rtpof=true&amp;sd=true\"><span style=\"color:#3498db\">klik tulisan ini ya!</span></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Penelitian juga dapat dilihat dengan mengunjungi Pameran Hakteknas yang bisa diakses lewat <a href=\"http://expo.icei.ac.id\"><span style=\"color:#3498db\">expo.icei.ac.id</span></a>&nbsp;sampai dengan 31 Agustus!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Selamat membaca!</p>\r\n', 'research,PenelitianKolaborasi,engagement,elearning,gap', 7, 27, 2, 'post', '62f9f509b548d.png', '2022-08-15 03:26:01', '2022-08-15 04:29:14', 166),
